description:
NRSectorCarrier:  A table containing configuration and operational parameters for individual NR sector carriers in a 5G network.

- dateTime: Timestamp indicating when the data was recorded.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographic area where the sector carrier is located.
- CellId: Unique identifier for the cell associated with the sector carrier.
- Id2: Duplicate of CellId.
- Id3: Secondary identifier for the sector carrier.
- vsDataType: Type of data contained in the row (constant value).
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
- NRSectorCarrier.ueAssistedPrecodingOptEnabled: Flag indicating if UE-assisted precoding is enabled.
- NRSectorCarrier.altitude: Altitude of the sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.pimAvoidDlMutingPeriod: Period for avoiding PIM during downlink muting.
- NRSectorCarrier.noOfTxAntennas: Number of transmit antennas.
- NRSectorCarrier.sectorEquipmentFunctionRef: Reference to the sector equipment function.
- NRSectorCarrier.powerMeasAvgTime: Average time for power measurements.
- NRSectorCarrier.noOfUsedTxAntennas: Number of used transmit antennas.
- NRSectorCarrier.arfcnUL: Uplink ARFCN (Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number).
- NRSectorCarrier.latitude: Latitude coordinates of the sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.essScLocalId: Local ID of the ESS (Enhanced Self-Organizing Network) SC (Sector Carrier).
- NRSectorCarrier.nRSectorCarrierId: Unique identifier for the NR sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.rfBranchTxRef: Reference to the transmit RF branch.
- NRSectorCarrier.txPowerPersistentLock: Flag indicating if transmit power is persistently locked.
- NRSectorCarrier.administrativeState: Administrative state of the sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.pimAvoidLevel: Level of PIM avoidance.
- NRSectorCarrier.arfcnDL: Downlink ARFCN.
- NRSectorCarrier.txPowerChangeRate: Rate of transmit power change.
- NRSectorCarrier.availabilityStatus: Availability status of the sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.scaledTransmissionPower: Scaled transmission power.
- NRSectorCarrier.ulCalibrationData: Uplink calibration data.
- NRSectorCarrier.longitude: Longitude coordinates of the sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.coverage: Coverage area of the sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.rfBranchRxRef: Reference to the receive RF branch.
- NRSectorCarrier.nullSteeringMode: Null steering mode.
- NRSectorCarrier.frequencyDL: Downlink frequency.
- NRSectorCarrier.frameStartOffset: Frame start offset.
- NRSectorCarrier.essScPairId: Pair ID of the ESS SC.
- NRSectorCarrier.radioTransmitPerfMode: Radio transmit performance mode.
- NRSectorCarrier.txPowerRatio: Transmit power ratio.
- NRSectorCarrier.bSChannelBwUL: Uplink channel bandwidth.
- NRSectorCarrier.configuredMaxTxPower: Configured maximum transmit power.
- NRSectorCarrier.pimDetectionEnabled: Flag indicating if PIM detection is enabled.
- NRSectorCarrier.dlCalibrationEnabled: Flag indicating if downlink calibration is enabled.
- NRSectorCarrier.dlCalibrationData: Downlink calibration data.
- NRSectorCarrier.noOfUsedRxAntennas: Number of used receive antennas.
- NRSectorCarrier.azimuthNull: Azimuth null.
- NRSectorCarrier.frequencyUL: Uplink frequency.
- NRSectorCarrier.polygon: Polygon representing the coverage area.
- NRSectorCarrier.bSChannelBwDL: Downlink channel bandwidth.
- NRSectorCarrier.cbrsEnabled: Flag indicating if CBRS (Citizens Broadband Radio Service) is enabled.
- NRSectorCarrier.reservedBy: Reference to the entity reserving the sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.noOfRxAntennas: Number of receive antennas.
- NRSectorCarrier.txDirection: Transmit direction (DL, UL, or both).
- NRSectorCarrier.operationalState: Operational state of the sector carrier.
- NRSectorCarrier.elevationNull: Elevation null.
- NRSectorCarrier.nRMicroSleepTxEnabled: Flag indicating if NR micro-sleep transmit is enabled.
- NRSectorCarrier.maxTransmissionPower: Maximum transmission power.
